obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (20937)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20937&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Food Security`
  line `Act, 2013.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided, it shall be deemed to have come into force on the 5th day of July,`
  line 2013.
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (20938)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20938&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(1) "anganwadi" means a child care and development center set up under the Integrated Child`
  line `Development Services Scheme of the Central Government to render services covered under section 4,`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 5 and section 6;`
  line
  line `(2) "central pool" means the stock of food grains which is,--`
  line
  line `(i) procured by the Central Government and the State Governments through minimum`
  line `support price operations;`
  line
  line `(ii) maintained for allocations under the Targeted Public Distribution System, other welfare`
  line `schemes, including calamity relief and such other schemes;`
  line
  line `(iii) kept as reserves for schemes referred to in sub-clause (ii);`
  line
  line `(3) "eligible households" means households covered under the priority households and the`
  line `Antyodaya Anna Yojana referred to in sub-section (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(4) "fair price shop" means a shop which has been licensed to distribute essential commodities by`
  line `an order issued under section 3 of the Essential Commodities Act, 1955 (10 of 1955), to the ration`
  line `card holders under the Targeted Public Distribution System;`
  line
  line `(5) "foodgrains" means rice, wheat or coarse grains or any combination thereof conforming to`
  line `such quality norms as may be determined, by order, by the Central Government from time to time;`
  line
  line `(6) "food security" means the supply of the entitled quantity of foodgrains and meal specified`
  line `under Chapter II;`
  line
  line `(7) "food security allowance" means the amount of money to be paid by the concerned State`
  line `Government to the entitled persons under section 8;`
  line
  line `(8) "local authority" includes Panchayat, municipality, district board, cantonment board, town`
  line `planning authority and in the States of Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya, Mizoram, Nagaland and Tripura`
  line `where Panchayats do not exist, the village council or committee or any other body, by whatever name`
  line `called, which is authorised under the Constitution or any law for the time being in force for self-`
  line `governance or any other authority or body vested with the control and management of civic services,`
  line `within a specified local area;`
  line
  line `(9) "meal" means hot cooked or pre-cooked and heated before its service meal or take home`
  line `ration, as may be prescribed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(10) "minimum support" price means the assured price announced by the Central Government at`
  line `which foodgrains are procured from farmers by the Central Government and the State Governments`
  line `and their agencies, for the central pool;`
  line
  line `(11) "notification" means a notification issued under this Act and published in the Official`
  line Gazette;
  line
  line `(12) "other welfare schemes" means such Government schemes, in addition to the Targeted`
  line `Public Distribution System, under which foodgrains or meals are supplied as part of the schemes;`
  line
  line `(13) "person with disability" means a person defined as such in clause (t) of section 2 of the`
  line `Persons with Disabilities (Equal Opportunities, Protection of Rights and Full Participation) Act, 1995`
  line `(1 of 1996);`
  line
  line `(14) "priority households" means households identified as such under section 10;`
  line
  line `(15) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(16) "ration card" means a document issued under an order or authority of the State Government`
  line `for the purchase of essential commodities from the fair price shops under the Targeted Public`
  line `Distribution System;`
  line
  line `(17) "rural area" means any area in a State except those areas covered by any urban local body or`
  line `a cantonment board established or constituted under any law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(18) "Schedule" means a Schedule appended to this Act;`
  line
  line `(19) "senior citizen" means a person defined as such under clause (h) of section 2 of the`
  line `Maintenance and Welfare of Parents and Senior Citizens Act, 2007 (56 of 2007);`
  line
  line `(20) "social audit" means the process in which people collectively monitor and evaluate the`
  line `planning and implementation of a programme or scheme;`
  line
  line `(21) "State Commission" means the State Food Commission constituted under section 16;`
  line
  line `(22) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the Administrator thereof`
  line `appointed under article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(23) "Targeted Public Distribution System" means the system for distribution of essential`
  line `commodities to the ration card holders through fair price shops;`
  line
  line `(24) "Vigilance Committee" means a committee constituted under section 29 to supervise the`
  line `implementation of all schemes under this Act;`
  line
  line `(25) the words and expressions not defined here but defined in the Essential Commodities Act,`
  line `1955 (10 of 1955), or any other relevant Act shall have the meaning respectively assigned to them in`
  line `those Acts.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (20939)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Right to receive foodgrains at subsidised prices by persons belonging to eligible households under Targeted Public Distribution System.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20939&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person belonging to priority households,`
  line `identified under sub-section (1) of section 10, shall be entitled to receive five kilograms of foodgrains per`
  line `person per month at subsidised prices specified in Schedule I from the State Government under the`
  line `Targeted Public Distribution System:`
  line
  line `Provided that the households covered under Antyodaya Anna Yojana shall, to such extent as may be`
  line `specified by the Central Government for each State in the said scheme, be entitled to thirty-five kilograms`
  line `of foodgrains per household per month at the prices specified in Schedule I:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if annual allocation of foodgrains to any State under the Act is less than the`
  line `average annual off take of foodgrains for last three years under normal Targeted Public Distribution`
  line `System, the same shall be protected at prices as may be determined by the Central Government and the`
  line `State shall be allocated foodgrains as specified in Schedule IV.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of this section, the "Antyodaya Anna" Yojana means, the scheme by`
  line `the said name launched by the Central Government on the 25th day of December, 2000; and as modified`
  line `from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) The entitlements of the persons belonging to the eligible households referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `at subsidised prices shall extend up to seventy-five per cent. of the rural population and up to fifty per`
  line `cent. of the urban population.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to sub-section (1), the State Government may provide to the persons belonging to eligible`
  line `households, wheat flour in lieu of the entitled quantity of foodgrains in accordance with such guidelines`
  line `as may be specified by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (20940)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Nutritional support to pregnant women and lactating mothers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20940&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such schemes as`
  line `may be framed by the Central Government, every pregnant woman and lactating mother shall be entitled`
  line to—
  line
  line `(a) meal, free of charge, during pregnancy and six months after the child birth, through the local`
  line `anganwadi, so as to meet the nutritional standards specified in Schedule II; and`
  line
  line `(b) maternity benefit of not less than rupees six thousand, in such instalments as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that all pregnant women and lactating mothers in regular employment with the Central`
  line `Government or State Governments or Public Sector Undertakings or those who are in receipt of`
  line `similar benefits under any law for the time being in force shall not be entitled to benefits specified in`
  line `clause (b).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (20941)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Nutritional support to children.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20941&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions contained in clause (b), every`
  line `child up to the age of fourteen years shall have the following entitlements for his nutritional needs,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of children in the age group of six months to six years, age appropriate meal, free`
  line `of charge, through the local anganwadi so as to meet the nutritional standards specified in Schedule`
  line `II:`
  line
  line `Provided that for children below the age of six months, exclusive breast feeding shall be`
  line promoted;
  line
  line `(b) in the case of children, up to class VIII or within the age group of six to fourteen years,`
  line `whichever is applicable, one mid-day meal, free of charge, everyday, except on school holidays, in all`
  line `schools run by local bodies, Government and Government aided schools, so as to meet the nutritional`
  line `standards specified in Schedule II.`
  line
  line `(2) Every school, referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1), and anganwadi shall have facilities for`
  line `cooking meals, drinking water and sanitation:`
  line
  line `Provided that in urban areas facilities of centralised kitchens for cooking meals may be used,`
  line `wherever required, as per the guidelines issued by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (20942)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Prevention and management of child malnutrition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20942&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall, through the`
  line `local anganwadi, identify and provide meals, free of charge, to children who suffer from malnutrition, so`
  line `as to meet the nutritional standards specified in Schedule II.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (20943)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Implementation of schemes for realisation of entitlements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20943&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The State Governments shall`
  line `implement schemes covering entitlements under sections 4, 5 and section 6 in accordance with the`
  line `guidelines, including cost sharing, between the Central Government and the State Governments in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (20944)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Right to receive food security allowance in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20944&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `In case of non-supply of the entitled`
  line `quantities of foodgrains or meals to entitled persons under Chapter II, such persons shall be entitled to`
  line `receive such food security allowance from the concerned State Government to be paid to each person,`
  line `within such time and manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (20945)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Coverage of population under Targeted Public Distribution System.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20945&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The percentage`
  line `coverage under the Targeted Public Distribution System in rural and urban areas for each State shall,`
  line `subject to sub-section (2) of section 3, be determined by the Central Government and the total number of`
  line `persons to be covered in such rural and urban areas of the State shall be calculated on the basis of the`
  line `population estimates as per the census of which the relevant figures have been published.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (20946)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `State Government to prepare guidelines and to identify priority households.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20946&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State`
  line `Government shall, within the number of persons determined under section 9 for the rural and urban areas,`
  line identify
  line
  line `(a) the households to be covered under the Antyodaya Anna Yojana to the extent specified under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3, in accordance with the guidelines applicable to the said scheme;`
  line
  line `(b) the remaining households as priority households to be covered under the Targeted Public`
  line `Distribution System, in accordance with such guidelines as the State Government may specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, as soon as possible, but within such period not`
  line `exceeding three hundred and sixty-five days, after the commencement of the Act, identify the eligible`
  line `households in accordance with the guidelines framed under this sub-section:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the State Government shall continue to receive the allocation of foodgrains`
  line `from the Central Government under the existing Targeted Public Distribution System, till the`
  line `identification of such households is complete.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall update the list of eligible households, within the number of persons`
  line `determined under section 9 for the rural and urban areas, in accordance with the guidelines framed under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (20947)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Publication and display of list of eligible households.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20947&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall place the`
  line `list of the identified eligible households in the public domain and display it prominently.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (20948)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Reforms in Targeted Public Distribution System.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20948&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central and State Governments`
  line `shall endeavour to progressively undertake necessary reforms in the Targeted Public Distribution System`
  line `in consonance with the role envisaged for them in this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The reforms shall, inter alia, include—`
  line
  line `(a) doorstep delivery of foodgrains to the Targeted Public Distribution System outlets;`
  line
  line `(b) application of information and communication technology tools including end-to-end`
  line `computerisation in order to ensure transparent recording of transactions at all levels, and to prevent`
  line diversion;
  line
  line `(c) leveraging ''aadhaar'' for unique identification, with biometric information of entitled`
  line `beneficiaries for proper targeting of benefits under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) full transparency of records;`
  line
  line `(e) preference to public institutions or public bodies such as Panchayats, selfhelp groups, cooperatives,`
  line `in licensing of fair price shops and management of fair price shops by women or their`
  line collectives;
  line
  line `(f) diversification of commodities distributed under the Public Distribution System over a period`
  line `of time;`
  line
  line `(g) support to local public distribution models and grains banks;`
  line
  line `(h) introducing schemes, such as, cash transfer, food coupons, or other schemes, to the targeted`
  line `beneficiaries in order to ensure their foodgrain entitlements specified in Chapter II, in such area and`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (20949)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Women of eighteen years of age or above to be head of household for purpose of issue of ration cards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20949&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The eldest woman who is not less than eighteen years of age, in every eligible`
  line `household, shall be head of the household for the purpose of issue of ration cards.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a household at any time does not have a woman or a woman of eighteen years of age or`
  line `above, but has a female member below the age of eighteen years, then, the eldest male member of the`
  line `household shall be the head of the household for the purpose of issue of ration card and the female`
  line `member, on attaining the age of eighteen years, shall become the head of the household for such ration`
  line `cards in place of such male member.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (20950)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Internal grievance redressal mechanism.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20950&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Every State Government shall put in place an`
  line `internal grievance redressal mechanism which may include call centres, help lines, designation of nodal`
  line `officers, or such other mechanism as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (20951)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `District Grievance Redressal Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20951&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall appoint or designate,`
  line `for each district, an officer to be the District Grievance Redressal Officer for expeditious and effective`
  line `redressal of grievances of the aggrieved persons in matters relating to distribution of entitled foodgrains`
  line `or meals under Chapter II, and to enforce the entitlements under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The qualifications for appointment as District Grievance Redressal Officer and its powers shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The method and terms and conditions of appointment of the District Grievance Redressal Officer`
  line `shall be such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government shall provide for the salary and allowances of the District Grievance`
  line `Redressal Officer and other staff and such other expenditure as may be considered necessary for their`
  line `proper functioning.`
  line
  line `(5) The officer referred to in sub-section (1) shall hear complaints regarding non-distribution of`
  line `entitled foodgrains or meals, and matters relating thereto, and take necessary action for their redressal in`
  line `such manner and within such time as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(6) Any complainant or the officer or authority against whom any order has been passed by officer`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1), who is not satisfied with the redressal of grievance may file an appeal`
  line `against such order before the State Commission.`
  line
  line `(7) Every appeal under sub-section (6) shall be filed in such manner and within such time as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (20952)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `State Food Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20952&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government shall, by notification, constitute a State`
  line `Food Commission for the purpose of monitoring and review of implementation of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Commission shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) five other Members; and`
  line
  line `(c) a Member-Secretary, who shall be an officer of the State Government not below the rank of`
  line `Joint Secretary to that Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that there shall be at least two women, whether Chairperson, Member or MemberSecretary:`
  line
  line `Provided further that there shall be one person belonging to the Scheduled Castes and one person`
  line `belonging to the Scheduled Tribes, whether Chairperson, Member or Member-Secretary.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson and other Members shall be appointed from amongst persons--`
  line
  line `(a) who are or have been member of the All India Services or any other civil services of the`
  line `Union or State or holding a civil post under the Union or State having knowledge and experience in`
  line `matters relating to food security, policy making and administration in the field of agriculture, civil`
  line `supplies, nutrition, health or any allied field; or`
  line
  line `(b) of eminence in public life with wide knowledge and experience in agriculture, law, human`
  line `rights, social service, management, nutrition, health, food policy or public administration; or`
  line
  line `(c) who have a proven record of work relating to the improvement of the food and nutrition rights`
  line `of the poor.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson and every other Member shall hold office for a term not exceeding five years`
  line `from the date on which he enters upon his office and shall be eligible for reappointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall hold office as the Chairperson or other Member after he has attained the`
  line `age of sixty-five years.`
  line
  line `(5) The method of appointment and other terms and conditions subject to which the Chairperson,`
  line `other Members and Member-Secretary of the State Commission may be appointed, and time, place and`
  line `procedure of meetings of the State Commission (including the quorum at such meetings) and its powers,`
  line `shall be such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The State Commission shall undertake the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) monitor and evaluate the implementation of this Act, in relation to the State;`
  line
  line `(b) either suo motu or on receipt of complaint inquire into violations of entitlements provided`
  line `under Chapter II;`
  line
  line `(c) give advice to the State Government on effective implementation of this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) give advice to the State Government, their agencies, autonomous bodies as well as nongovernmental`
  line `organisations involved in delivery of relevant services, for the effective implementation`
  line `of food and nutrition related schemes, to enable individuals to fully access their entitlements specified`
  line `in this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) hear appeals against orders of the District Grievance Redressal Officer;`
  line
  line `(f) prepare annual reports which shall be laid before the State Legislature by the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(7) The State Government shall make available to the State Commission, such administrative and`
  line `technical staff, as it may consider necessary for proper functioning of the State Commission.`
  line
  line `(8) The method of appointment of the staff under sub-section (7), their salaries, allowances and`
  line `conditions of service shall be such, as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(9) The State Government may remove from office the Chairperson or any Member who--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or at any time has been, adjudged as an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a member; or`
  line
  line `(c) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the State Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `a member; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuation in office detrimental to the public`
  line interest.
  line
  line `(10) No such Chairperson or Member shall be removed under clause (d) or clause (e) of sub-section (9) unless he has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (20953)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Salary and allowances of Chairperson, Member, Member-Secretary and other staff of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20953&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall provide for salary and allowances of Chairperson, other`
  line `Members, Member-Secretary, support staff, and other administrative expenses required for proper`
  line `functioning of the State Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (20954)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Designation of any Commission or body to function as State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20954&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The State`
  line `Government may, if considers it necessary, by notification, designate any statutory commission or a body`
  line `to exercise the powers and perform the functions of the State Commission referred to in section 16.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (20955)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Joint State Food Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20955&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 16, two or more States may have a Joint State Food Commission for the purposes of this Act with`
  line `the approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (20956)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Powers relating to inquiries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20956&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Commission shall, while inquiring into any matter`
  line `referred to in clauses (b) and (e) of sub-section (6) of section 16, have all the powers of a civil court while`
  line `trying a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) and, in particular, in respect of the`
  line `following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office; and`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Commission shall have the power to forward any case to a Magistrate having`
  line `jurisdiction to try the same and the Magistrate to whom any such case is forwarded shall proceed to hear`
  line `the complaint against the accused as if the case has been forwarded to him under section 346 of the Code`
  line `of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (20957)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20957&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of`
  line `the State Commission shall be invalid merely by reason of—`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the State Commission; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person as the Chairperson or a Member of the State`
  line `Commission; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the State Commission not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (20958)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Central Government to allocate required quantity of foodgrains from central pool to State Governments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20958&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, for ensuring the regular supply of foodgrains to`
  line `persons belonging to eligible households, allocate from the central pool the required quantity of`
  line `foodgrains to the State Governments under the Targeted Public Distribution System, as per the`
  line `entitlements under section 3 and at prices specified in Schedule I.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall allocate foodgrains in accordance with the number of persons`
  line `belonging to the eligible households identified in each State under section 10.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall provide foodgrains in respect of entitlements under sections 4, 5`
  line `and section 6, to the State Governments, at prices specified for the persons belonging to eligible`
  line `households in Schedule I.`
  line
  line `(4) Without prejudice to sub-section (1), the Central Government shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) procure foodgrains for the central pool through its own agencies and the State Governments`
  line `and their agencies;`
  line
  line `(b) allocate foodgrains to the States;`
  line
  line `(c) provide for transportation of foodgrains, as per allocation, to the depots designated by the`
  line `Central Government in each State;`
  line
  line `(d) provide assistance to the State Government in meeting the expenditure incurred by it towards`
  line `intra-State movement, handling of foodgrains and margins paid to fair price shop dealers, in`
  line `accordance with such norms and manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(e) create and maintain required modern and scientific storage facilities at various levels.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (20959)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Provisions for funds by Central Government to State Government in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20959&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `In case`
  line `of short supply of foodgrains from the central pool to a State, the Central Government shall provide funds`
  line `to the extent of short supply to the State Government for meeting obligations under Chapter II in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (20960)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Implementation and monitoring of schemes for ensuring food security.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20960&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State`
  line `Government shall be responsible for implementation and monitoring of the schemes of various Ministries`
  line `and Departments of the Central Government in accordance with guidelines issued by the Central`
  line `Government for each scheme, and their own schemes, for ensuring food security to the targeted`
  line `beneficiaries in their State.`
  line
  line `(2) Under the Targeted Public Distribution System, it shall be the duty of the State Government to—`
  line
  line `(a) take delivery of foodgrains from the designated depots of the Central Government in the State,`
  line `at the prices specified in Schedule I, organise intra-State allocations for delivery of the allocated`
  line `foodgrains through their authorised agencies at the door-step of each fair price shop; and`
  line
  line `(b) ensure actual delivery or supply of the foodgrains to the entitled persons at the prices specified`
  line `in Schedule I.`
  line
  line `(3) For foodgrain requirements in respect of entitlements under sections 4, 5 and section 6, it shall be`
  line `the responsibility of the State Government to take delivery of foodgrains from the designated depots of`
  line `the Central Government in the State, at the prices specified in Schedule I for persons belonging to eligible`
  line `households and ensure actual delivery of entitled benefits, as specified in the aforesaid sections.`
  line
  line `(4) In case of non-supply of the entitled quantities of foodgrains or meals to entitled persons under`
  line `Chapter II, the State Government shall be responsible for payment of food security allowance specified in`
  line `section 8.`
  line
  line `(5) For efficient operations of the Targeted Public Distribution System, every State Government`
  line shall,—
  line
  line `(a) create and maintain scientific storage facilities at the State, District and Block levels, being`
  line `sufficient to accommodate foodgrains required under the Targeted Public Distribution System and`
  line `other food based welfare schemes;`
  line
  line `(b) suitably strengthen capacities of their Food and Civil Supplies Corporations and other`
  line `designated agencies;`
  line
  line `(c) establish institutionalised licensing arrangements for fair price shops in accordance with the`
  line `relevant provisions of the Public Distribution System (Control) Order, 2001 made under the Essential`
  line `Commodities Act, 1955 (10 of 1955), as amended from time.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (20961)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Implementation of Targeted Public Distribution System by local authority in their areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20961&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The local authorities shall be responsible for the proper implementation of this Act in their respective`
  line areas.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to sub-section (1), the State Government may assign, by notification, additional`
  line `responsibilities for implementation of the Targeted Public Distribution System to the local authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (20962)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Obligations of local authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20962&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `In implementing different schemes of the Ministries and`
  line `Departments of the Central Government and the State Governments, prepared to implement provisions of`
  line `this Act, the local authorities shall be responsible for discharging such duties and responsibilities as may`
  line `be assigned to them, by notification, by the respective State Governments.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (20963)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Disclosure of records of Targeted Public Distribution System.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20963&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `All Targeted Public`
  line `Distribution System related records shall be placed in the public domain and kept open for inspection to`
  line `the public, in such manner as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (20964)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Conduct of social audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20964&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every local authority, or any other authority or body, as may be`
  line `authorised by the State Government, shall conduct or cause to be conducted, periodic social audits on the`
  line `functioning of fair price shops, Targeted Public Distribution System and other welfare schemes, and cause`
  line `to publicise its findings and take necessary action, in such manner as may be prescribed by the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, if it considers necessary, conduct or cause to be conducted social`
  line `audit through independent agencies having experience in conduct of such audits.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (20965)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Setting up of Vigilance Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20965&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) For ensuring transparency and proper functioning of`
  line `the Targeted Public Distribution System and accountability of the functionaries in such system, every`
  line `State Government shall set up Vigilance Committees as specified in the Public Distribution System`
  line `(Control) Order, 2001, made under the Essential Commodities Act, 1955 (10 of 1955), as amended from`
  line `time to time, at the State, District, Block and fair price shop levels consisting of such persons, as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government giving due representation to the local authorities, the Scheduled`
  line `Castes, the Scheduled Tribes, women and destitute persons or persons with disability.`
  line
  line `(2) The Vigilance Committees shall perform the following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) regularly supervise the implementation of all schemes under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) inform the District Grievance Redressal Officer, in writing, of any violation of the`
  line `provisions of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(c) inform the District Grievance Redressal Officer, in writing, of any malpractice or`
  line `misappropriation of funds found by it.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (20966)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Food security for people living in remote, hilly and tribal areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20966&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government`
  line `and the State Governments shall, while implementing the provisions of this Act and the schemes for`
  line `meeting specified entitlements, give special focus to the needs of the vulnerable groups especially in`
  line `remote areas and other areas which are difficult to access, hilly and tribal areas for ensuring their food`
  line security.
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (20967)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Steps to further advance food and nutritional security.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20967&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government, the State`
  line `Governments and local authorities shall, for the purpose of advancing food and nutritional security, strive`
  line `to progressively realise the objectives specified in Schedule III.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (20968)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Other welfare schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20968&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Act shall not preclude the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government from continuing or formulating other food based welfare schemes.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the State Government may, continue with or`
  line `formulate food or nutrition based plans or schemes providing for benefits higher than the benefits`
  line `provided under this Act, from its own resources.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (20969)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20969&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Any public servant or authority found guilty, by the State Commission at the time of`
  line `deciding any complaint or appeal, of failing to provide the relief recommended by the District`
  line `Grievance Redressal Officer, without reasonable cause, or wilfully ignoring such recommendation, shall`
  line `be liable to penalty not exceeding five thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the public servant or the public authority, as the case may be, shall be given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard before any penalty is imposed.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (20970)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to adjudicate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20970&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of adjudging penalty under section 33, the State`
  line `Commission shall authorise any of its member to be an adjudicating officer for holding an inquiry in the`
  line `prescribed manner after giving any person concerned a reasonable opportunity of being heard for the`
  line `purpose of imposing any penalty.`
  line
  line `(2) While holding an inquiry the adjudicating officer shall have power to summon and enforce the`
  line `attendance of any person acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case to give evidence or to`
  line `produce any document which in the opinion of the adjudicating officer, may be useful for or relevant to`
  line `the subject matter of the inquiry and if, on such inquiry, he is satisfied that the person has failed to`
  line `provide the relief recommended by the District Grievance Redressal Officer, without reasonable cause, or`
  line `wilfully ignored such recommendation, he may impose such penalty as he thinks fit in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of section 33.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (20971)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to delegate by Central Government and State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20971&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, direct that the powers exercisable by it (except the power to make`
  line `rules), in such circumstances and subject to such conditions and limitations, be exercisable also by the`
  line `State Government or an officer subordinate to the Central Government or the State Government as it may`
  line `specify in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by notification, direct that the powers exercisable by it (except the`
  line `power to make rules), in such circumstances and subject to such conditions and limitations, be exercisable`
  line `also by an officer subordinate to it as it may specify in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (20972)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20972&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act or the schemes made thereunder shall`
  line `have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being`
  line `in force or in any instrument having effect by virtue of such law.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (20973)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power to amend Schedules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20973&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do, it may, by notification, amend Schedule I or Schedule II or Schedule III or Schedule`
  line `IV and thereupon Schedule I or Schedule II or Schedule III or Schedule IV, as the case may be, shall be`
  line `deemed to have been amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification issued under sub-section (1), shall be laid before each House of`
  line `Parliament as soon as may be after it is issued.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (20974)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20974&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, from time to`
  line `time, give such directions, as it may consider necessary, to the State Governments for the effective`
  line `implementation of the provisions of this Act and the State Governments shall comply with such`
  line directions.
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (20975)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20975&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, in`
  line `consultation with the State Governments and by notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) scheme including cost sharing for providing maternity benefit to pregnant women and`
  line `lactating mothers under clause (b) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) schemes covering entitlements under sections 4, 5 and section 6 including cost sharing under`
  line `section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) amount, time and manner of payment of food security allowance to entitled individuals under`
  line `section 8;`
  line
  line `(d) introducing schemes of cash transfer, food coupons or other schemes to the targeted`
  line `beneficiaries in order to ensure their foodgrains entitlements in such areas and manner under clause`
  line `(h) of sub-section (2) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(e) the norms and manner of providing assistance to the State Governments in meeting`
  line `expenditure under clause (d) of sub-section (4) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(f) manner in which funds shall be provided by the Central Government to the State Governments`
  line `in case of short supply of foodgrains, under section 23;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed or in respect of which provision is to be`
  line `made by the Central Government by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (20976)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20976&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification,`
  line `and subject to the condition of previous publication, and consistent with this Act and the rules made by`
  line `the Central Government, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) guidelines for identification of priority households under sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(b) internal grievance redressal mechanism under section 14;`
  line
  line `(c) qualifications for appointment as District Grievance Redressal Officer and its powers under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(d) method and terms and conditions of appointment of the District Grievance Redressal Officer`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(e) manner and time limit for hearing complaints by the District Grievance Redressal Officer and`
  line `the filing of appeals under sub-sections (5) and (7) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(f) method of appointment and the terms and conditions of appointment of Chairperson, other`
  line `Members and Member-Secretary of the State Commission, procedure for meetings of the`
  line `Commission and its powers, under sub-section (5) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(g) method of appointment of staff of the State Commission, their salaries, allowances and`
  line `conditions of service under sub-section (8) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(h) manner in which the Targeted Public Distribution System related records shall be placed in`
  line `the public domain and kept open for inspection to public under section 27;`
  line
  line `(i) manner in which the social audit on the functioning of fair price shops, Targeted Public`
  line `Distribution System and other welfare schemes shall be conducted under section 28;`
  line
  line `(j) composition of Vigilance Committees under sub-section (1) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(k) schemes or programmes of the Central Government or the State Governments for utilisation of`
  line `institutional mechanism under section 43;`
  line
  line `(l) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed or in respect of which provision is to be`
  line `made by the State Government by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule, notification and guidelines made or issued by the State Government under this Act`
  line `shall, as soon as may be after it is made or issued, be laid before each House of the State Legislature`
  line `where there are two Houses, and where there is one House of the State Legislature, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (20977)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Transitory provisions for schemes, guidelines, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20977&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `The schemes, guidelines, orders and food`
  line `standard, grievance redressal mechanism, vigilance committees, existing on the date of commencement of`
  line `this Act, shall continue to be in force and operate till such schemes, guidelines, orders and food standard,`
  line `grievance redressal mechanism, vigilance committees are specified or notified under this Act or the rules`
  line `made thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that anything done or any action taken under the said schemes, guidelines, orders and food`
  line `standard, grievance redressal mechanism, or by vigilance committees shall be deemed to have been done`
  line `or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act and shall continue to be in force accordingly`
  line `unless and until superseded by anything done or by any action taken under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (20978)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20978&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (20979)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Utilisation of institutional mechanism for other purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20979&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The services of authorities to be`
  line `appointed or constituted under sections 15 and 16 may be utilised in the implementation of other schemes`
  line `or programmes of the Central Government or the State Governments, as may be prescribed by the State`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (20980)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Force Majeure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20980&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government, or as the case may be, the State Government, shall be`
  line `liable for a claim by any person entitled under this Act, except in the case of war, flood, drought, fire,`
  line `cyclone or earthquake affecting the regular supply of foodgrains or meals to such person under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, in consultation with the Planning Commission, declare`
  line `whether or not any such situation affecting the regular supply of foodgrains or meals to such person has`
  line `arisen or exists.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (20981)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638&sectionId=20981&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_000010_201320_1517807327638
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Food Security Ordinance, 2013 (Ord. 7 of 2013) is`
  line `hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal,—`
  line
  line `(a) anything done, any action taken or any identification of eligible households made; or`
  line
  line `(b) any right, entitlement, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred; or`
  line
  line `(c) any guidelines framed or directions issued; or`
  line
  line `(d) any investigation, inquiry or any other legal proceeding initiated, conducted or continued in`
  line `respect of such right, entitlement, privilege, obligation or liability as aforesaid; or`
  line
  line `(e) any penalty imposed in respect of any offence,`
  line
  line `under the said Ordinance shall be deemed to have been done, taken, made, acquired, accrued, incurred,`
  line `framed, issued, initiated, conducted, continued or imposed under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
